The paper deals with energy consumption in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific focus on multi-hop radio networks and communication primitives suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of randomized and deterministic algorithms and the consideration of collision detection and leader election suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-categories. Finally, the tradeoff between energy and time complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
